    <!-- How We Tested -->
    <section>
      <h2>How We Tested These Creatine Gummies</h2>

      <div class="tested-box">
        <h3>Our Testing Methodology</h3>
        <p>We purchased all 31 creatine gummies with our own money. No brand provided free samples or paid for placement. Our testing protocol spans 12 weeks and evaluates each product across five weighted categories.</p>
        <ol>
          <li><strong>Dosage Accuracy (30% weight)</strong> — We verified the creatine content per serving against label claims using independent COA (Certificate of Analysis) data where available. Products delivering the full 5g clinical dose scored highest.</li>
          <li><strong>Third-Party Testing (25% weight)</strong> — We prioritized products with recognized certifications: NSF Certified for Sport, Informed Sport, USP Verified, or equivalent independent lab verification. Uncertified products received lower scores.</li>
          <li><strong>Taste and Texture (20% weight)</strong> — A panel of 8 testers scored each product on flavor quality, sweetness balance, texture, and aftertaste using a blind protocol. Scores were averaged and normalized.</li>
          <li><strong>Ingredient Transparency (15% weight)</strong> — We evaluated full ingredient lists, allergen disclosures, added sugar content, artificial additive usage, and clarity of labeling. Clean-label products with fewer additives scored higher.</li>
          <li><strong>Value (10% weight)</strong> — We calculated the cost per gram of creatine, per serving, and per 30-day supply. Products delivering more creatine per dollar ranked higher.</li>
        </ol>
      </div>
    </section>

